President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Oklahoma due to severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred between April 30 and May 1, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Gerard M. Stolar has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are still ongoing, and more counties and types of assistance may be designated once the assessments are completed. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.